title: Total white blood cells 0_01
characteristics_ch1: cell type: Total white blood cells
characteristics_ch1.1: sorted by surface marker: unsorted
characteristics_ch1.2: pooled or single individual?: single individual
description: total white blood cells enriched from total peripheral blood through red blood cell lysis, then either directly resuspended in Trizol (unsorted) or stained with antibodies for sort
description.1: Cells were stained with following antibodies: CD33 PE (BD Bioscience 555450), CD34 APC (BD Bioscience 555824), CD3 FITC (BD Bioscience 555332), CD19 PE-Cy7 (BD Bioscience 557835), CD14 APC-Cy (BioLegend 325620) and PI for 30 minutes in the dark
description.2: cells were sorted on a BD Aria Sorter. First, different populations were gated according to FSC/SSC, then further defined by positivity for CD33, CD3, CD19, CD34 and CD14 as indicated above.
data_processing.1: Sequenced reads were trimmed for adaptor sequence and mapped to the reference genome using CASAVA 1.8.2
data_processing.2: Reads Per Kilobase of exon per Megabase of library size (RPKM) were calculated using CASAVA 1.8.2
data_processing.4: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab-delimited text files include RPKM values for each sample. Columns are: Chromosome, Start location, Stop location, Gene, RPKM, base count.
contact_institute: Institute for Research in Immunology and Cancer

data_processing.1: Sequenced reads were trimmed for adaptor sequence and mapped to the reference genome using CASAVA 1.8.2
data_processing.2: Reads Per Kilobase of exon per Megabase of library size (RPKM) were calculated using CASAVA 1.8.2
data_processing.4: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab-delimited text files include RPKM values for each sample. Columns are: Chromosome, Start location, Stop location, Gene, RPKM, base count.
contact_institute: Institute for Research in Immunology and Cancer
